[font=Courier New][b][size=140][color=DarkOrange]I guess there is nothing wrong in reading facts![/color][/size][/b]

[hide][size=120][b]-[color=Red]Base Of the  ROM & Version?[/color]
->Roms is Based on AOSP

-[COLOR="red"]Why no "Incremental updates" Support?[/COLOR]
->Actually the updates we provide monthly are heavily changed and modified than the previous builds. New stuffs are merged and added. So we don't provide incremental updates and recommend clean flash.
 
 
-[color=Red]Does this ROM Support Substratum/CMTE?[/color]
->Yes, full substratum support!
 
-[color=Red]Which Gapps are recommended?[/color]
->OpenGapps or
->BeansGApps
 
-[color=Red]What about XPOSED?[/color]
->XPOSED For N is not out yet. Still in Development. We like Xposed but it messes up with the system so before giving any bug reports make sure you have xposed uninstalled.
 
-[color=Red]What about custom Kernels?
[/color]->You are free to try out available kernels,but in case of any bugs,we will not support.
 
-[color=red]When Will Be the Next Update?[/color]
->No ETAs please. ROM Will be updated whenever the new build is ready. We generally provide monthly updates with latest security patches and new features.

-[COLOR="red"]Adaway is not working :([/COLOR]
->Download it from here [URL="https://forum.xda-developers.com/showthread.php?t=2190753"]Adaway[/URL]

-[COLOR="red"]SElinux Linux mode changer app is not working nor Busy Box installer app is working.[/COLOR]
->It is everything good with the sources. You should try other things first and then contact your maintainer.
 
-[color=red]I am facing FCs, Bugs, Some feature is broken?[/color]
->Provide Full info About your problem with logcats and the procedure to reproduce it.
->How to take Logcats?
   [url]https://goo.gl/UcTM9[/url]
 
-[color=red]I want to contribute To the Development of this ROM?[/color]
->Join our G+ community:
->Join our telegram Group
->Pull Requests on Github[/b][/size][/hide][/font][/align]

